>NAME

_glidix_xperm - get permission sets.

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <sys/xperm.h>
	
	xperm_t _glidix_oxperm();
	xperm_t _glidix_dxperm();

>DESCRIPTION

Those functions return the own permission set, and the delegatable permsision set of the calling thread, respectively. See [xperm.6] for more information on permissions.

>RETURN VALUE

Those functions are always successful and return the own or delegatable permission sets of the calling thread.

